# Railway Deployment

## Project Details

- Railway project: `cursor-web-v2`
- Service: `cursor-web-v2`
- Domain: `cursorremote.up.railway.app`
- GitHub repo linked for auto-deploy on push to `main`

## Railway CLI

### Installation

Railway CLI is invoked via npx (no global install needed):

```
npx @railway/cli@latest <command>
```

### Common Commands

```powershell
# Check status
npx @railway/cli@latest status

# View deployment logs (live tail)
npx @railway/cli@latest logs

# List all services
npx @railway/cli@latest service list

# Link local project to Railway (interactive)
npx @railway/cli@latest link

# Manual deploy (upload local code)
npx @railway/cli@latest up

# Open Railway dashboard
npx @railway/cli@latest open

# View environment variables
npx @railway/cli@latest variables

# Set environment variable
npx @railway/cli@latest variables set KEY=VALUE

# View deployment domain
npx @railway/cli@latest domain
```

### Deployment Methods

1. **Auto-deploy (preferred)**: Push to GitHub → Railway auto-deploys
   ```
   git add -A && git commit -m "message" && git push
   ```

2. **Manual deploy**: Upload current directory
   ```
   npx @railway/cli@latest up
   ```

### Important Notes

- Railway uses `npm start` which runs `node server/index.js`
- The PORT env var is set by Railway (usually 8080), the server reads `process.env.PORT || 3000`
- Railway's localhost is NOT your local machine -- CDP connections to `localhost:9222` won't work on Railway
- Health check endpoint: `GET /health`
- Debug endpoint: `GET /debug/sessions` (shows MCP session state)

### Troubleshooting

- **"Application not found"**: Railway is mid-redeploy. Wait 30-60 seconds and retry.
- **Logs show no CDP connections**: Expected on Railway. CDP only works when server runs locally.
- **MCP sessions stuck in "unbound"**: The agent hasn't called `wait_for_response` yet, or sessions expired.
- **Deploy not picking up changes**: Ensure `.gitignore` excludes `node_modules`, then push to trigger auto-deploy.

### Testing Railway Deployment

```powershell
# Health check
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri https://cursorremote.up.railway.app/health

# MCP session debug info
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri https://cursorremote.up.railway.app/debug/sessions

# Verify MCP endpoint responds
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri https://cursorremote.up.railway.app/mcp -Method POST -ContentType "application/json" -Body '{}'
```

### PowerShell Gotchas

- Use `Invoke-RestMethod` or `Invoke-WebRequest` instead of `curl` (PowerShell aliases `curl` to `Invoke-WebRequest` which has different syntax)
- Pipe characters `|` in URL parameters need quoting or encoding
- Use Node.js scripts for complex API testing instead of PowerShell one-liners
